The '''2018 American salmonella outbreak''' was an American [[disaster]] in which over 250 people<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wgntv.com/2018/04/09/salmonella-in-chicken-salad-kills-1-sickens-265-in-8-states/|title=Salmonella in chicken salad kills 1, sickens 265 in 8 states|date=2018-04-09|work=WGN-TV|access-date=2018-04-11|language=en-US}}</ref> were sickened by chicken salad contaminated with [[salmonella]]. Other outbreaks were confirmed with turkey identified as the cause.

== Timeline ==
The chicken salad was made by an Iowa-based food processing company Triple T Specialty Meats and distributed in [[Fareway]] supermarket.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/salmonella/typhimurium-02-18/index.html|title=Multistate Outbreak of Salmonella Typhimurium Linked to Chicken Salad {{!}} February 2018 {{!}} Salmonella {{!}} CDC|date=2018-04-06|website=www.cdc.gov|language=en-us|access-date=2018-04-11}}</ref>  One person in [[Iowa]] died, and more than 90 others were [[hospital]]ized.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.desmoinesregister.com/story/news/health/2018/04/09/tainted-chicken-salad-fareway-iowa-womans-death/499765002/|title=CDC ties tainted chicken salad to Iowan's death. State expert says salad may not be to blame.|work=Des Moines Register|access-date=2018-04-11|language=en}}</ref> At least 48 lawsuits have been filed against Triple-T and Fareway from outbreak victims.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/salmonella-chicken-salad-kills-1-sickens-265-8-states-n864071|title=Salmonella-contaminated chicken salad kills 1, sickens 265 across 8 states|newspaper=NBC News|accessdate=2018-04-11}}</ref>

It was reported by the [[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|Center for Disease Control and Prevention]] that since last November 164 people had fallen ill in 35 states due to raw turkey. No products were recalled, and the CDC issued a reminder for individuals to properly cook and handle turkey.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/ny-news-salmonella-turkey-death-cdc-20181110-story.html|title=164 sickened and one dead in ongoing turkey salmonella outbreak: CDC - NY Daily News|last=Press|first=The Associated|work=nydailynews.com|access-date=2018-11-11|language=en-US}}</ref>

