The following are national '''[[holiday]]s in [[Paraguay]]'''<ref>{{Cite document| title = Calendario Escolar Año Lectivo 2012| place = Asuncion| publisher = Ministerio de Educación y Culto, Paraguay| year = 2011| url = http://www.mec.gov.py/cms/entradas/291966-calendario-escolar-ano-lectivo-2012| postscript = <!--None-->| deadurl = yes| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120824080027/http://www.mec.gov.py/cms/entradas/291966-calendario-escolar-ano-lectivo-2012| archivedate = August 24, 2012| df = mdy-all}}</ref>
{| class="wikitable" ! Date !! English Name !! Local Name !! Remarks |- |January 1 || New Year || || |- |March 1 || Heroes' Day || Dia de los héroes || Moved to February 27 for 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ultimahora.com/establecen-traslados-feriados-el-2017-n1042098.html |title=Establecen traslados de feriados para el 2017 |publisher=[[Diario Ultima Hora]] |accessdate=February 20, 2017}}</ref> |- |March/ April || Maundy/Holy Thursday || Jueves Santo || Movable, Lunar Calendar. April 12 on 2017. |- |March/ April || Good Friday || Viernes Santo || Movable, Lunar Calendar. April 13 on 2017. |- |May 1 || [[International Workers' Day|Labor Day]] || Día de los Trabajadores || |- |May 14 || [[Independence of Paraguay|Paraguayan Independence Day]] || Independencia || |- |June 12 || [[Chaco Armistice Day]] || Dia de la Paz del Chaco || End of the Chaco War. |- |August 15 || Founding of [[Asunción]] || Fundación de Asunción || Arrival of the Spaniards. Moved to August 14 for 2017. |- |September 29 || [[Battle of Boquerón (1932)|Boqueron Battle]] Victory Day || Victoria de Boquerón || [[Chaco War]] decisive Paraguayan victory. Moved to October 2 for 2017. |- |December 8 || Virgin of Caacupe || Virgen de Caacupé || Immaculate Conception |- |December 25 || [[Christmas Day]] || Día de Navidad || |}
+ Fixed holidays: all holidays in Paraguay can be moved by presidential decree, but there has to be a presidential decree for such a change. The following holidays are the exception (dates are fixed and to not change): January 1st, May 14, December 8, December 25, Maundy Thursday and Good Friday.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://paraguay.justia.com/nacionales/leyes/ley-1723-jun-29-2001/gdoc/ |title=Ley 1.723/2001 Que autoriza al poder ejecutivo a trasladar los feriados nacionales al día Lunes |publisher=[[Congreso de la Nación Paraguaya]] |accessdate=February 1, 2016}}</ref>
